==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hendecane
<hw>Hen"de*cane</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>"e`ndeka</grk> eleven.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
hydrocarbon, <chform>C11H24</chform>, of the paraffin series; -- so
called because it has eleven atoms of carbon in each molecule. Called
also <altname>endecane</altname>, <altname>undecane</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

